VP Han said the heroic deeds of the Flying Tigers have always remained deep in the hearts of the Chinese people, and we'll never forget our old friends. Over 80 years ago, China and the US fought shoulder to shoulder against fascism, and the stories of Flying Tigers testify to the profound friendship forged between our peoples with life and blood. In the world today, China-US cooperation remains vital for addressing many major challenges. The two countries need to respect each other, coexist in peace and pursue win-win cooperation, so as to contribute more to world peace and development. VP Han expressed his hope that the spirit of Flying Tigers will be passed down from generation to generation.

result.text:
On Oct. 27, FM Wang Yi and NSA @JakeSullivan46 had a substantive and constructive strategic communication on China-US relations, high-level exchanges, and international and regional issues of common concern including the Palestinian-Israeli conflict.

The two sides agreed to make joint efforts toward a meeting between the two Presidents in San Francisco. FM Wang pointed it out that "Taiwan independence" is the biggest threat to peace and stability across the Taiwan Strait and the biggest challenge facing China-US relations. It must be firmly opposed with concrete policies and actions. He also stated China's position on the South China Sea. The two sides agreed to maintain strategic communication.
